1
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:24,140
=Manbo Destiny=

2
00:00:24,140 --> 00:00:25,700
=Episode 24=

3
00:00:32,085 --> 00:00:32,816
Father.

4
00:00:39,739 --> 00:00:40,778
I heard

5
00:00:41,547 --> 00:00:42,624
that under your leadership,

6
00:00:44,008 --> 00:00:45,278
post-disaster reconstruction

7
00:00:45,470 --> 00:00:46,432
has progressed rapidly.

8
00:00:46,893 --> 00:00:48,085
The smiles of the people,

9
00:00:48,355 --> 00:00:49,662
the vitality of the villages,

10
00:00:50,355 --> 00:00:51,739
are all thanks to you.

11
00:00:52,162 --> 00:00:52,816
As your father,

12
00:00:53,432 --> 00:00:54,778
I am proud of you.

13
00:00:56,393 --> 00:00:57,124
Father.

14
00:00:58,085 --> 00:00:59,739
This is merely my duty.

15
00:01:03,239 --> 00:01:03,970
It is time

16
00:01:04,470 --> 00:01:05,739
that I hand over the throne

17
00:01:07,085 --> 00:01:08,085
to you.

18
00:01:09,970 --> 00:01:10,624
Father.

19
00:01:11,162 --> 00:01:12,855
This country still needs your guidance.

20
00:01:13,393 --> 00:01:14,047
How could you...

21
00:01:15,047 --> 00:01:16,316
This is not impulsive.

22
00:01:17,124 --> 00:01:19,239
I have thought it through carefully.

23
00:01:21,470 --> 00:01:22,393
Manbo Kingdom

24
00:01:23,239 --> 00:01:24,893
needs young people like you,

25
00:01:25,162 --> 00:01:26,085
innovative

26
00:01:26,701 --> 00:01:29,355
and truly devoted to its people.

27
00:01:29,778 --> 00:01:30,970
The future of this world

28
00:01:31,855 --> 00:01:33,585
belongs to the young people.

29
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:02,405
Breaking News.

30
00:02:02,405 --> 00:02:04,058
The King announces
he will step down as Regent.

31
00:02:04,058 --> 00:02:05,943
The throne will be passed
to First Prince Song Pai.

32
00:02:05,943 --> 00:02:07,635
The First Prince is deeply loved
by the people.

33
00:02:07,635 --> 00:02:09,866
The coronation ceremony
will be held soon.

34
00:02:47,166 --> 00:02:49,012
- Long live the King!
- Long live the King!

35
00:02:49,012 --> 00:02:50,705
- Long live the Queen!
- Long live the Queen!

36
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,884
Rise.

37
00:03:04,730 --> 00:03:06,038
The Queen and I

38
00:03:07,884 --> 00:03:10,192
along with my brother,
Prince Lin Ge, the Regent,

39
00:03:11,769 --> 00:03:13,038
hereby swear an oath

40
00:03:14,269 --> 00:03:15,769
that we will lead Manbo Kingdom

41
00:03:16,115 --> 00:03:17,461
toward a brighter future

42
00:03:19,115 --> 00:03:20,500
and guide its people

43
00:03:21,346 --> 00:03:22,615
toward modernization

44
00:03:23,884 --> 00:03:25,654
and a happier life.

45
00:03:27,538 --> 00:03:29,577
- Long live the King!
- Long live the King!

46
00:03:29,577 --> 00:03:31,360
- Long live the Queen!
- Long live the Queen!

47
00:03:31,577 --> 00:03:33,692
- Long live the King!
- Long live the King!

48
00:03:33,692 --> 00:03:35,807
- Long live the Queen!
- Long live the Queen!

49
00:03:48,307 --> 00:03:50,230
Your Majesty, please have some tea.

50
00:03:51,346 --> 00:03:52,000
Thank you.

51
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:57,038
Why are there still so many documents
to review?

52
00:03:57,692 --> 00:03:59,346
Don't you feel sorry for His Majesty?

53
00:03:59,654 --> 00:04:00,577
Your Majesty.

54
00:04:00,577 --> 00:04:02,769
We truly care about His Majesty.

55
00:04:03,307 --> 00:04:05,730
So we prepared albums of beauties
from across the land

56
00:04:05,730 --> 00:04:07,120
for His Majesty to choose a consort.

57
00:04:07,961 --> 00:04:08,730
What?

58
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:10,654
Choose a consort?

59
00:04:10,654 --> 00:04:11,269
No.

60
00:04:11,807 --> 00:04:12,500
Take them away.

61
00:04:12,769 --> 00:04:13,538
Let me see.

62
00:04:25,038 --> 00:04:25,961
This one looks nice.

63
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,230
They're all pretty.

64
00:04:33,423 --> 00:04:34,038
These...

65
00:04:34,269 --> 00:04:35,230
This one is good too.

66
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,077
I don't need this.

67
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,077
Take them away at once.

68
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,307
However, Miss Emily

69
00:04:40,923 --> 00:04:42,961
who returned from Portugal has arrived.

70
00:04:43,038 --> 00:04:43,807
Emily?

71
00:04:44,577 --> 00:04:45,192
Who is she?

72
00:04:47,077 --> 00:04:49,307
She said Your Majesty used
to call her "Little Millet".

73
00:04:54,077 --> 00:04:57,230
Little Millet?
I remember she was quite short.

74
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:59,038
She was actually quite cute as a child.

75
00:05:01,615 --> 00:05:02,461
No need to see her.

76
00:05:04,307 --> 00:05:04,846
Come back!

77
00:05:06,307 --> 00:05:06,730
Of course.

78
00:05:07,961 --> 00:05:09,230
You must see her.

79
00:05:10,269 --> 00:05:12,692
She came all the way from Portugal

80
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,654
and she's an old acquaintance.

81
00:05:17,115 --> 00:05:18,423
You must see her.

82
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:40,700
Hello, my Prince.

83
00:05:47,230 --> 00:05:48,884
Help her up quickly.

84
00:05:49,730 --> 00:05:50,654
Get up.

85
00:05:51,692 --> 00:05:53,884
Song Pai, long time no see.

86
00:05:54,115 --> 00:05:55,307
I came to keep our promise.

87
00:05:57,577 --> 00:05:58,423
A promise?

88
00:05:59,307 --> 00:06:01,269
You personally promised me
when we were young

89
00:06:01,654 --> 00:06:04,115
that you would marry me
and make me queen.

90
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,160
Children's words don't count.

91
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,115
Besides,

92
00:06:10,423 --> 00:06:12,000
I already have a queen now.

93
00:06:12,654 --> 00:06:13,654
Song Pai.

94
00:06:14,077 --> 00:06:16,923
I don't mind sharing you
with other women.

95
00:06:16,923 --> 00:06:18,192
After all, you are the king.

96
00:06:19,077 --> 00:06:21,115
I have long been prepared for this.

97
00:06:22,207 --> 00:06:23,130
Wonderful!

98
00:06:23,822 --> 00:06:26,014
You two talk, I'll take my leave.

99
00:06:26,822 --> 00:06:27,514
Mengmeng.

100
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:30,014
Song Pai.

101
00:06:30,014 --> 00:06:30,553
No.

102
00:06:30,553 --> 00:06:31,553
Song Pai.

103
00:06:33,668 --> 00:06:34,437
Mengmeng.

104
00:06:35,399 --> 00:06:36,245
Don't go.

105
00:06:36,745 --> 00:06:37,514
Let go!

106
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:39,399
Let go of me!

107
00:06:42,476 --> 00:06:43,130
Mengmeng!

108
00:06:47,860 --> 00:06:48,591
Little Millet.

109
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:51,091
Thank you for holding me
in such high regard.

110
00:06:51,322 --> 00:06:52,168
But

111
00:06:52,399 --> 00:06:53,668
right now, my heart

112
00:06:54,168 --> 00:06:55,745
belongs to Mengmeng alone.

113
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:57,976
I have no intention
of taking concubines.

114
00:06:59,553 --> 00:07:00,360
Song Pai.

115
00:07:00,668 --> 00:07:01,784
If one day

116
00:07:01,784 --> 00:07:02,899
you change your mind,

117
00:07:02,899 --> 00:07:03,899
remember to let me know.

118
00:07:04,130 --> 00:07:06,380
I'll be here waiting for you.

119
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:08,707
That day will never come.

120
00:07:11,476 --> 00:07:12,053
Mengmeng.

121
00:07:27,437 --> 00:07:29,399
What exactly are you trying to do?

122
00:07:30,168 --> 00:07:31,668
Every time that guy makes you mad,

123
00:07:31,668 --> 00:07:32,976
you take it out on me.

124
00:07:33,322 --> 00:07:33,860
Besides,

125
00:07:35,130 --> 00:07:37,822
the king putting a huge bounty
on you isn't my fault.

126
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,620
(This isn't right.)

127
00:07:42,976 --> 00:07:44,784
(A ten-million Manbo Coins bounty.)

128
00:07:46,553 --> 00:07:47,976
(Why shouldn't I earn it?)

129
00:07:55,630 --> 00:07:56,437
Look.

130
00:07:56,591 --> 00:07:57,937
He apologized to you.

131
00:07:57,937 --> 00:07:58,591
Look.

132
00:08:00,514 --> 00:08:01,207
Mengmeng.

133
00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:03,399
Come back.

134
00:08:04,822 --> 00:08:06,822
I swear to all the people of Manbo.

135
00:08:07,591 --> 00:08:09,514
I will love only you
for the rest of my life.

136
00:08:10,553 --> 00:08:11,822
I will be faithful only to you.

137
00:08:13,091 --> 00:08:14,053
Come home, okay?

138
00:08:14,784 --> 00:08:15,937
I'll wait for you.

139
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:28,988
The Queen?

140
00:08:29,796 --> 00:08:31,027
Isn't this the Queen?

141
00:08:31,334 --> 00:08:33,680
I'm going to claim the bounty
from His Majesty.

142
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:34,873
What are you talking about?

143
00:08:34,873 --> 00:08:35,873
The reward is mine.

144
00:08:35,873 --> 00:08:37,334
What does it have to do with you? Go!

145
00:08:37,334 --> 00:08:38,296
Mind your own business.

146
00:08:38,450 --> 00:08:39,296
Mengmeng.

147
00:08:39,911 --> 00:08:40,565
Wait for me.

148
00:08:43,334 --> 00:08:44,180
I don't care.

149
00:08:44,450 --> 00:08:45,834
Even if we turn Manbo upside down,

150
00:08:45,834 --> 00:08:47,757
you must find the Queen for me.

151
00:08:48,757 --> 00:08:49,527
Song Pai.

152
00:08:49,796 --> 00:08:50,680
Wanida said

153
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:52,334
she knows why Mengmeng won't come back.

154
00:08:53,527 --> 00:08:54,257
Wanida.

155
00:08:55,527 --> 00:08:57,950
Why isn't Sister Mengmeng coming back?

156
00:08:58,219 --> 00:09:00,565
You have to go there to find her.

157
00:09:01,834 --> 00:09:03,104
I understand, Wanida.

158
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:04,296
I'll be going now.

159
00:09:07,180 --> 00:09:08,834
Good luck, brother!

160
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:20,642
Chase her!

161
00:09:20,642 --> 00:09:21,680
She's over there.

162
00:09:23,334 --> 00:09:23,911
Your Majesty!

163
00:09:23,911 --> 00:09:25,642
I found the Queen first!

164
00:09:25,642 --> 00:09:28,180
I found her first!

165
00:09:28,180 --> 00:09:30,219
I'm going to claim the reward!

166
00:09:30,219 --> 00:09:31,142
Your Majesty!

167
00:09:36,219 --> 00:09:36,757
Mengmeng.

168
00:09:37,027 --> 00:09:37,873
Don't be mad anymore.

169
00:09:38,873 --> 00:09:39,411
I'm sorry.

170
00:09:41,257 --> 00:09:42,296
Don't be angry.

171
00:09:42,834 --> 00:09:43,988
Go find your Little Millet.

172
00:09:43,988 --> 00:09:45,565
I have a gift for you.

173
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,027
Don't think that just because
you give me a gift,

174
00:09:48,027 --> 00:09:49,296
I'll forgive you.

175
00:09:55,796 --> 00:09:57,104
Didn't I throw this away?

176
00:09:57,373 --> 00:09:58,527
How did you find it?

177
00:09:58,873 --> 00:10:00,296
After you threw it away that day,

178
00:10:01,296 --> 00:10:02,450
I picked it back up.

179
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:18,746
I always feel that this necklace

180
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,354
and what lies between us

181
00:10:21,431 --> 00:10:23,008
are deeply intertwined.

182
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:26,020
Look.

183
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:37,954
Princess Mengzhen, Guan Xinrui

184
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,800
pays respects to Your Majesty.

185
00:10:41,223 --> 00:10:42,607
Are you the princess

186
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:44,646
sent by Mengzhen?

187
00:10:45,877 --> 00:10:47,030
Yes, Your Majesty.

188
00:10:48,069 --> 00:10:52,030
Lift your head and let me have a look.

189
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,877
You're beautiful as a butterfly
from the heavens.

190
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:36,492
I am deeply pleased.

191
00:11:45,684 --> 00:11:47,107
So it turns out this story

192
00:11:47,607 --> 00:11:49,338
was beautiful from the very beginning.

193
00:11:52,338 --> 00:11:54,684
I thought this necklace brought us

194
00:11:55,569 --> 00:11:58,107
nothing but pain and suffering.

195
00:11:59,069 --> 00:12:00,723
So I threw it away,

196
00:12:01,838 --> 00:12:03,531
thinking everything would get better.

197
00:12:04,723 --> 00:12:06,146
Perhaps its true meaning

198
00:12:06,761 --> 00:12:08,069
was never to separate us,

199
00:12:08,531 --> 00:12:10,646
but to test us,

200
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:12,880
so we could find each other again.

201
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:30,100
I've heard snakes
symbolize reincarnation,

202
00:12:30,523 --> 00:12:32,138
and signifying the continuation of fate.

203
00:12:32,530 --> 00:12:34,408
Maybe in a past life,
we couldn't be together.

204
00:12:35,484 --> 00:12:36,408
But in this life,

205
00:12:36,408 --> 00:12:37,946
the pendant guided us to meet again,

206
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,080
to complete our destiny.

207
00:12:39,754 --> 00:12:40,446
Song Pai.

208
00:12:41,523 --> 00:12:43,984
Are you really willing to try again,

209
00:12:43,984 --> 00:12:45,715
even if we might be hurt again,

210
00:12:46,254 --> 00:12:47,023
and lose everything?

211
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:49,177
No matter how many times,

212
00:12:51,523 --> 00:12:52,984
as long as I can be with you,

213
00:12:55,677 --> 00:12:56,408
I'm willing.

214
00:13:26,177 --> 00:13:27,061
What does this mean?

215
00:13:27,715 --> 00:13:29,484
Medical leave for one week.

216
00:13:29,754 --> 00:13:31,292
The Regent will act in your place.

217
00:13:32,446 --> 00:13:33,638
You really came up with this.

218
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:34,984
Your body is stronger than an ox.

219
00:13:38,369 --> 00:13:39,484
Say something.

220
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:54,177
Baofan.

221
00:14:20,660 --> 00:14:24,260
(A new story is about to begin)

222
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:33,700
♪I do this for you♪

223
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:36,340
♪The love is fake♪

224
00:14:36,740 --> 00:14:39,100
♪The love is true♪

225
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:41,980
♪For you♪
